\section{FLT and Euler's theorem}
 Both Fermat's Little Theorem (FLT) and Euler's Theorem are fundamental in the number theory branch of math. FLT is related to Euler's theorem because it is possible, in fact, to use Euler's theorem in order to prove FLT.
 NOTE: Do not confuse Fermat's Little Theorem with Fermat's Last theorem even though both of them can be abbreviated to FLT.
